The error you are encountering is due to the fact that the `LinkedHashMap` is not guaranteed to have more elements after the first call to `iterator().next()`. To avoid this issue, you can use the `hasNext()` method to check if there are more elements before calling `next()`. Here's the updated code:
```java
Set<String> windowsid = driver.getWindowHandles();
Iterator<String> iterate = windowsid.iterator();
while (iterate.hasNext()) {
    String windowId = iterate.next();
    System.out.println(windowId);
}
String mainwindow_id = iterate.next();
String tabbedwindow_id = iterate.next();
```
With this change, the code should work without throwing a `NoSuchElementException`.
